{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_07_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "G in the Air",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 0.928,
  "page_end_sec": 241.34,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.77,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.36,
      "end": 4.08,
      "text": " CHAPTER VII OF THE MALTESE FALCON by Dashiell Hammett"
    },
    {
      "start": 4.08,
      "end": 7.6,
      "text": " This LibriVox recording is in the public domain."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.28,
      "end": 9.86,
      "text": " G. In the Air"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.58,
      "end": 17.08,
      "text": "In his bedroom that was a living-room now the wall-bed was up, Spade took Brigid O'Shaughnessy's",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 17.08,
      "end": 22.6,
      "text": " hat and coat, made her comfortable in a padded rocking chair, and telephoned the Hotel Belvedere."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.34,
      "end": 28.26,
      "text": " Cairo had not returned from the theatre. Spade left his telephone-number with the request"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.26,
      "end": 30.64,
      "text": " that Cairo call him as soon as he came in."
    },
    {
      "start": 31.744,
      "end": 33.78,
      "text": "Spade sat down in the armchair beside",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 33.78,
      "end": 35.88,
      "text": "the table and without any preliminary,"
    },
    {
      "start": 36.56,
      "end": 38.64,
      "text": "without an introductory remark of any sort,"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.84,
      "end": 41.6,
      "text": "began to tell the girl about a thing that had happened"
    },
    {
      "start": 41.72,
      "end": 43.24,
      "text": "some years before in the Northwest."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.88,
      "end": 47.64,
      "text": "He talked in a steady matter-of-fact voice that was devoid of"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.72,
      "end": 48.72,
      "text": "emphasis or pauses,"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.34,
      "end": 50.86,
      "text": "though now and then he repeated a"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.86,
      "end": 53.24,
      "text": "sentence slightly rearranged, as if it were"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.36,
      "end": 57.52,
      "text": "important that each detail be related exactly as it had happened."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.62,
      "end": 59.22,
      "text": "At the beginning",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 59.4,
      "end": 59.84,
      "text": "Brigid"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.02,
      "end": 62.36,
      "text": "O'Shaughnessy listened with only partial attentiveness,"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.61,
      "end": 64.48,
      "text": "obviously more surprised by his"
    },
    {
      "start": 64.58,
      "end": 66.2,
      "text": "telling the story than interested in it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.34,
      "end": 69.38,
      "text": "her curiosity more engaged with his purpose in"
    },
    {
      "start": 69.38,
      "end": 71.82,
      "text": "telling the story than with the story he told;"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.18,
      "end": 73.3,
      "text": "but presently,"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.3,
      "end": 74.5,
      "text": "as the story went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.6,
      "end": 75.16,
      "text": "it caught"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.16,
      "end": 76.16,
      "text": "her more and more fully"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.72,
      "end": 78.06,
      "text": "and she became still and receptive."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.2,
      "end": 80.86,
      "text": "A man named Flitcraft had left",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 80.92,
      "end": 83.2,
      "text": "his real-estate-office, in Tacoma, to go to"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.2,
      "end": 85.26,
      "text": "luncheon one day and had never returned."
    },
    {
      "start": 85.81,
      "end": 87.1,
      "text": "He did not keep an"
    },
    {
      "start": 87.22,
      "end": 89.3,
      "text": "engagement to play golf after four that afternoon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.88,
      "end": 91.9,
      "text": "though he had taken the initiative in making the"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.0,
      "end": 95.4,
      "text": "engagement less than half an hour before he went out to luncheon."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.32,
      "end": 97.68,
      "text": "His wife and children never saw"
    },
    {
      "start": 97.68,
      "end": 98.14,
      "text": "him again."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.84,
      "end": 101.24,
      "text": "His wife and he were supposed to be on the best of terms."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.54,
      "end": 102.8,
      "text": "He had two children,"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.02,
      "end": 103.47,
      "text": "boys,"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.96,
      "end": 104.44,
      "text": "one five"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.88,
      "end": 105.54,
      "text": "and the other three."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.1,
      "end": 108.58,
      "text": "He owned his house in a Tacoma suburb,"
    },
    {
      "start": 109.08,
      "end": 109.67,
      "text": "a new Packard,"
    },
    {
      "start": 109.92,
      "end": 110.78,
      "text": "and the rest of"
    },
    {
      "start": 110.98,
      "end": 113.56,
      "text": "the appurtenances of successful American living."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.624,
      "end": 117.7,
      "text": "Flitcraft had inherited seventy thousand dollars from his father,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 117.9,
      "end": 118.3,
      "text": "and,"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.52,
      "end": 120.18,
      "text": "with his success in real estate,"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.72,
      "end": 123.6,
      "text": "was worth something in the neighborhood of two hundred thousand dollars"
    },
    {
      "start": 123.88,
      "end": 125.22,
      "text": "at the time he vanished."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.24,
      "end": 127.26,
      "text": "His affairs were in order,"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.7,
      "end": 129.52,
      "text": "though there were enough loose ends to"
    },
    {
      "start": 129.6,
      "end": 131.18,
      "text": "indicate that he had not been setting"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.18,
      "end": 133.16,
      "text": "them in order preparatory to vanishing."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.16,
      "end": 134.96,
      "text": "A deal that would"
    },
    {
      "start": 134.96,
      "end": 136.62,
      "text": "have brought him an attractive profit,"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.76,
      "end": 137.16,
      "text": "for instance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.74,
      "end": 139.18,
      "text": "was to have been concluded the day"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.34,
      "end": 141.4,
      "text": "after the one on which he disappeared."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.4,
      "end": 144.88,
      "text": "There was nothing to suggest that he had more than fifty or"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.96,
      "end": 146.72,
      "text": "sixty dollars in his immediate possession"
    },
    {
      "start": 147.34,
      "end": 148.36,
      "text": "at the time of his going."
    },
    {
      "start": 149.24,
      "end": 150.44,
      "text": "His habits for months past"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.64,
      "end": 153.22,
      "text": "could be accounted for too thoroughly to justify"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.22,
      "end": 156.76,
      "text": "any suspicion of secret vices, or even of another"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.9,
      "end": 157.84,
      "text": "woman in his life,"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.32,
      "end": 160.0,
      "text": "though either was barely possible."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.94,
      "end": 161.78,
      "text": "\"He went like that,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 162.02,
      "end": 162.78,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 163.34,
      "end": 163.58,
      "text": "\"like a"
    },
    {
      "start": 163.64,
      "end": 164.94,
      "text": "fist when you open your hand.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 166.06,
      "end": 167.84,
      "text": "When he had reached this point in his story",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 167.9,
      "end": 168.88,
      "text": "the telephone-bell rang."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.04,
      "end": 172.56,
      "text": "\"Hello,\" Spade said into the instrument.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 173.2,
      "end": 173.52,
      "text": "\"Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.62,
      "end": 174.02,
      "text": "Cairo?"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.7,
      "end": 175.29,
      "text": ". . . This is Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.88,
      "end": 177.32,
      "text": "Can you come up to my place—"
    },
    {
      "start": 178.304,
      "end": 178.7,
      "text": "Post Street—"
    },
    {
      "start": 179.22,
      "end": 180.08,
      "text": "now?"
    },
    {
      "start": 180.56,
      "end": 181.16,
      "text": ". . . Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.18,
      "end": 182.24,
      "text": "I think it is.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 182.62,
      "end": 183.74,
      "text": "He looked at the girl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 183.88,
      "end": 184.78,
      "text": "pursed his lips,"
    },
    {
      "start": 184.86,
      "end": 185.86,
      "text": "and then said rapidly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 186.94,
      "end": 189.344,
      "text": "\"Miss O'Shaughnessy is here and wants to see you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 190.272,
      "end": 192.66,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy frowned and stirred in her chair,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 192.98,
      "end": 194.2,
      "text": "but did not say anything."
    },
    {
      "start": 195.392,
      "end": 197.24,
      "text": "Spade put the telephone down and told her:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 197.98,
      "end": 199.0,
      "text": "\"He'll be up in a few minutes."
    },
    {
      "start": 199.66,
      "end": 200.36,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 200.6,
      "end": 201.98,
      "text": "that was in 1922."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.1,
      "end": 204.1,
      "text": "In 1927"
    },
    {
      "start": 204.18,
      "end": 207.04,
      "text": "I was with one of the big detective agencies in Seattle."
    },
    {
      "start": 207.78,
      "end": 208.12,
      "text": "Mrs."
    },
    {
      "start": 208.18,
      "end": 211.38,
      "text": "Flitcraft came in and told us somebody had seen a man in Spokane"
    },
    {
      "start": 211.62,
      "end": 213.18,
      "text": "who looked a lot like her husband."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.06,
      "end": 214.8,
      "text": "I went over there."
    },
    {
      "start": 215.76,
      "end": 216.48,
      "text": "It was Flitcraft,"
    },
    {
      "start": 216.62,
      "end": 216.96,
      "text": "all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.56,
      "end": 220.55,
      "text": "He had been living in Spokane for a couple of years as Charles—that was his first"
    },
    {
      "start": 221.4,
      "end": 222.3,
      "text": "name—Pierce."
    },
    {
      "start": 222.48,
      "end": 222.86,
      "text": "Pierce."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.9,
      "end": 225.62,
      "text": "He had an automobile-business that was"
    },
    {
      "start": 225.62,
      "end": 227.94,
      "text": "netting him twenty or twenty-five thousand a year,"
    },
    {
      "start": 228.12,
      "end": 229.02,
      "text": "a wife,"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.2,
      "end": 230.02,
      "text": "a baby son,"
    },
    {
      "start": 230.37,
      "end": 232.7,
      "text": "owned his home in a Spokane suburb,"
    },
    {
      "start": 233.02,
      "end": 234.94,
      "text": "and usually got away to play golf after"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.94,
      "end": 236.84,
      "text": "four in the afternoon during the season.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 237.856,
      "end": 239.52,
      "text": "Spade had not been told very definitely",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 239.52,
      "end": 241.34,
      "text": "what to do when he found Flitcraft."
    }
  ]
}